Sailor (South America)
Sailors of the South American coastline operate the boats, trading vessels,
and patrol craft that knit the region's coastal communities together. They
are skilled mariners and practical fighters who have navigated some of the
most dangerous waters on post-Rifts Earth.

Sailors choose from Pilot, Physical, Technical, and Rogue skill categories.
They are trained in seamanship, navigation, maintenance, and the particular
diplomacy required when every port has different rules.

Attribute requirements: PS 9, PE 9.
Starting equipment: Sailor's clothing, waterproof pack, personal radio,
navigation charts, a utility knife, one week of rations, and standard
maritime equipment.
